#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:2
msgid "Cross compilation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:4
msgid ""
"Cross compilation is a complex topic, we only add some hopefully helpful "
"hints here (for now). As of May 2025, cross-compilation with a Meson cross "
"file as well as cross-compilation based on ``crossenv`` are known to work. "
"Conda-forge uses the latter method. Cross-compilation without ``crossenv`` "
"requires passing build options to ``meson setup`` via `meson-python`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:12
msgid ""
"All distributions that are known to successfully cross compile NumPy are "
"using ``python -m build`` (``pypa/build``), but using ``pip`` for that "
"should be possible as well. Here are links to the NumPy \"build recipes\" on "
"those distros:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:17
msgid ""
"`Void Linux <https://github.com/void-linux/void-packages/blob/master/srcpkgs/"
"python3-numpy/template>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:18
msgid ""
"`Nix <https://github.com/NixOS/nixpkgs/tree/master/pkgs/development/python-"
"modules/numpy>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:19
msgid ""
"`Conda-forge <https://github.com/conda-forge/numpy-feedstock/blob/main/"
"recipe/build.sh>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:21
msgid ""
"See also `Meson's documentation on cross compilation <https://mesonbuild.com/"
"Cross-compilation.html>`__ to learn what options you may need to pass to "
"Meson to successfully cross compile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:25
msgid ""
"One possible hiccup is that the build requires running a compiled executable "
"in order to determine the ``long double`` format for the host platform. This "
"may be an obstacle, since it requires ``crossenv`` or QEMU to run the host "
"(cross) Python. To avoid this problem, specify the paths to the relevant "
"directories in your *cross file*:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:31
msgid ""
"[properties]\n"
"longdouble_format = 'IEEE_DOUBLE_LE'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:36
msgid ""
"For an example of a cross file needed to cross-compile NumPy, see "
"`numpy#288861 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/"
"issues/28861#issuecomment-2844257091>`__. Putting that together, invoking a "
"cross build with such a cross file, looks like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:40
msgid ""
"$ python -m build --wheel -Csetup-args=\"--cross-file=aarch64-myos-cross-"
"file.txt\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:44
msgid "For more details and the current status around cross compilation, see:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:46
msgid ""
"The state of cross compilation in Python: `pypackaging-native key issue page "
"<https://pypackaging-native.github.io/key-issues/cross_compilation/>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../building/cross_compilation.rst:48
msgid ""
"The `set of NumPy issues with the \"Cross compilation\" label <https://"
"github.com/numpy/numpy/issues?q=state%3Aclosed%20label%3A%2238%20-"
"%20Cross%20compilation%22>`__"
msgstr ""

